      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 151: restart() clears backoff state without cancelling the pending retry timer. resetConnectionBackoff() already clears the map and cancels the timer, but restart() only calls resetConnectionBackoff() while shutdown() separately calls cancelBackoffRetry(). If restart() is called without a prior shutdown path that cancelled the timer, an old timer can still fire and run maintainBuckets() unexpectedly on the restarted manager. Prefer making restart() explicitly cancel via resetConnectionBackoff() only if that method is guaranteed to cancel, or keep the cancellation here documented and covered by test.\n```suggestion\nvoid\nSwarmManager::restart()\n{\n    isShutdown_ \u003d false;\n    resetConnectionBackoff();\n}\n```",
