      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 181: setConnectionBackoffForTest() accepts zero or inverted durations, which can create immediate retry loops or make every failure expire incorrectly. Even for test-only hooks, this mutates production state and should enforce sane values so accidental misuse does not destabilize the retry timer.\n```suggestion\nvoid setConnectionBackoffForTest(std::chrono::milliseconds base, std::chrono::milliseconds max)\n{\n    if (base \u003c\u003d std::chrono::milliseconds::zero() || max \u003c base)\n        throw std::invalid_argument(\"invalid connection backoff window\");\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex);\n    backoffBase_ \u003d base;\n    backoffMax_ \u003d max;\n}\n```",
